<paragraph id="2845BDCE360C1CB601603A99B7668AF0" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Female (n = 14). Body length 4.1-6.0 mm, polished, coriaceous, covered with silver setae.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="5E81DA022D782DE25C282FC6FCFA9135" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="FCC8B3BBA0F56E86BF347BC47F8016A9" bold="true" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Head</emphasis>
0.5 
<normalizedToken id="0B1D4DD211ECF9BA1E74ADC740CFB19C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as wide. Clypeus 2.1-2.4 
<normalizedToken id="412B159925DE29CC0104CAC37B6EA8AC" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as high, flat in lateral view. Face 1.88-2.2 
<normalizedToken id="66275AC3D74B5C971E88807E8DD98EA8" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as broad as high, densely punctate, convex medially in lateral view, separated from clypeus by shallow clypeal sulcus. Inner orbits almost parallel (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="8B39740E5F13084E7297145C05E8340B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4B</figureCitation>
). Length of malar space 1.1-1.15
<normalizedToken id="81DA822875E026F3A08EC9617211150D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as basal mandibular width. POL 2.0-2.1 
<normalizedToken id="9E0459494CBE07F3953F45F0C3097B62" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OD. OOL 1.0-1.2 
<normalizedToken id="B4A241F075EF0D952A2592666C8C8069" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OD. POL 2.0-2.2 
<normalizedToken id="CB1E5B216AB4D324128ADD1E551EC06E" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as OOL. Antenna with 20-21 flagellomeres. FL I 1.15-1.35 
<normalizedToken id="6BEC54565FC83CA3A86107D0B788960B" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as FL II. MP IV 1.45-1.66 
<normalizedToken id="A546843B93CBB8B6602F0E032CEE1D09" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as MP V.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AF9930D14F441CB0DB7F16C1D0F5A1A" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="38A8A94B3478944F7469EBAE6C9AE473" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="E2705F9B4AD39FE915E883333F64581F" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Mesosoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
Lateral aspect of pronotum rugulose anteriorly. Mesoscutum densely punctate (separated by ca. 0.5-1.0 
<normalizedToken id="11061058756FC0D61989A33BDBA2893D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their diameter) (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="82F484A2233F4300B7FB6F9CF9DA4A95" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4C</figureCitation>
). Scutellum finely and sparsely punctate (separated by ca. 1.5-2.0 
<normalizedToken id="2ED56F52EE2DC5C2AEF1FBB3DA1A9D8A" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
their diameter). Lower part of mesopleuron coarsely and sparsely punctate. Sternaulus indistinct. Propodeum without rugae and carinae (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="58A41AA74F6A1616840D8E790078817A" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4D</figureCitation>
), rounded in lateral view. Fore wing length 4.0-5.0 mm. Nervellus intercepted below middle. Hind femur 3.75-4.0 
<normalizedToken id="872B53CB2D85B47DE9487AC298B2B15C" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Hind tibia 8.0-9.5 
<normalizedToken id="A2DA19FA0820C65FA4119233102D5D4D" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum depth in lateral view. Ratio of length of hind first to fifth tarsomeres 1.0: 0.6: 0.5: 0.3: 0.25-0.3.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D43A2C916DB87AF35587A1C8B0B1BA96" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="DECE7A0E63623D58D77BBBA5B8FA7C56" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="4D545705B7C889DCE900048347DF3983" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Metasoma</emphasis>
.
</emphasis>
T I square in dorsal view (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="D45DAED6DD6D4D9A90D7217ADD450515" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9H</figureCitation>
), 1.0-1.1 
<normalizedToken id="E01D26875D515CE18136761D860B99D1" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum width, rugulose laterally. Latero-median carina present basal ca. 0.3 of T I (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="7473F80B7C7AE7C08234E07E044A0D30" captionStart="Figure 9" captionStartId="F9" captionText="Figure 9. Japanese Woldstedtius A, G. W. f. flavolineatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); B, I. W. kuroashii (Uchida, 1957); C, D, K. W. takagii (Uchida, 1957); E. W. alpicola sp. nov.; F. W. biguttatus (Gravenhorst, 1829); H. W. karafutensis (Uchida, 1957); J. W. punctatus sp. nov. (E, J. holotype; B, I. paratype) - A, B. head, lateral view; C. head, frontal view; D. propodeum, lateral view; E-K. T I, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure9" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667929" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">9H</figureCitation>
). T II 0.86-1.0 
<normalizedToken id="9362413FFCC74047041E6920F338D4FF" originalValue="×">x</normalizedToken>
as long as maximum width, strigose except for posterior margin smooth.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64770978C1CC7446D5C2F890DF6816C6" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="F4C52DF64CC6DD3F23429C423BCF3D73" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="C30F882D95954E8F9959550DD4124D72" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Coloration</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="DC36D4188C899E0F0A681E6A859A27D3" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4A-D</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body (excluding wings and legs) black to blackish-brown. Face with a large white median spot (this spot connected with white clypeus). Clypeus, palpi, tegula, subtegular ridge, upper mesepisternum and scutellum white. Mandible white, except for apex and base. Lateral aspect of pronotum with a white spot posteriorly. Antenna brown. Veins and pterostigma yellowish-brown to brown. Legs whitish-yellow. Hind coxa with a dorsal blackish-brown stripe. Hind femur brown. Hind tibia and tarsomere black. Base of hind tibia tinged with white.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="168AD845C2A8B850268DFF9E7F86C357" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="043E64F1A2B72890441E73A4DCE58689" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Male (n = 2).</emphasis>
Similar to female. Inner orbits weakly divergent downward (Fig. 
<figureCitation id="5AFA937C215060982946C6BAAF70EA01" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4F</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="92CB14EBD1BA7B89428C316E3B2F8BEE" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="CBF0C2587CA7D4DB9369E12806B82049" bold="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
<emphasis id="C0374E9B2D0AF309774D4EA26EE9F352" italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Coloration</emphasis>
(Fig. 
<figureCitation id="A1E2EC8626A2F3BEFA9D3AC2A04C063B" captionStart="Figure 4" captionStartId="F4" captionText="Figure 4. Woldstedtius karafutensis (Uchida, 1957) (A-D. female; E, F. male) - A, E. Habitus; B, F. Head, frontal view; C. Mesonotum, dorsal view; D. Propodeum, dorsal view." figureDoi="10.3897/dez.69.80492.figure4" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/667924" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">4E, F</figureCitation>
).
</emphasis>
Body (excluding wings and legs) black to blackish-brown. Clypeus, palpi, face, ventral surface of antenna, malar space, propleuron, epicnemium, mesosternum, tegula, subtegular ridge, upper mesepisternum and scutellum white. Gena tinged with white ventrally. Mandible white except for apex. Lateral aspect of pronotum tinged with white ventrally and posteriorly. Mesoscutum with white shoulder marks. Mesopleuron with a large white marking; it is enlarged anteriorly. Wings hyaline. Veins and pterostigma yellowish-brown to brown. Legs white. Fore and mid tarsi, apex of hind trochantellus, base and apex of hind femur and hind tarsomeres brown. Hind coxa with a dorsal brown stripe. Hind tibia tinged with brown.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="4F59F97C60F7DD692C8F6ABE33952829" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="301C403FF0D8F8954BFCC4892DD4CFD9" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="64A6343B41A899751A7FBCF2D058E4A9" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">
Japan (Hokkaido and Honshu). Outside Japan, this species has been recorded from Russia and South Korea (
<bibRefCitation id="B05299AF1EF99075F28120EF776017C9" DOI="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2016.04.012" author="Balueva, EN" journalOrPublisher="Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" pagination="387 - 397" refId="B1" refString="Balueva, EN, Lee, JW, 2016. Study of the genus Woldstedtius Carlson (Hymenoptera; Ichneumonidae; Diplazontinae) with description of three new species in South Korea. Journal of Asia-Pacific Entomology 19 (2): 387 - 397, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2016.04.012" title="Study of the genus Woldstedtius Carlson (Hymenoptera; Ichneumonidae; Diplazontinae) with description of three new species in South Korea." url="https://doi.org/10.1016/j.aspen.2016.04.012" volume="19" year="2016">Balueva and Lee 2016</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation id="A9636B7A564CCEBA760823F7C204E8C8" author="Yu, DS" journalOrPublisher="Folia Entomologica Hungarica" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" refId="B25" refString="Yu, DS, van Achterberg, K, Horstmann, K, 2016. World Ichneumonoidea 2015. Taxonomy, biology, morphology and distribution. [Database on flash drive]. Taxapad, Vancouver." title="World Ichneumonoidea 2015. Taxonomy, biology, morphology and distribution. [Database on flash drive]. Taxapad, Vancouver." year="2016">Yu et al. 2016</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="48BD736227F8A9F8CD5D4571610CF2E1" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="bionomics">
<paragraph id="E7F7F625D58090F375F20F9D3590AA98" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Bionomics.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="19D108B15AEFF09C9313EA6BDB95459F" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Host unknown.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="8E3EA03DC7ED7F9F8B473D2F580B2111" pageId="0" pageNumber="45" type="remarks">
<paragraph id="60803337BCB324CB7E6FE23664DE9C7A" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">Remarks.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C307CD32461132B8CA117F8BC0FA0A37" pageId="0" pageNumber="45">This is the first record of this species from Honshu.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
